{"parse":{"title":"Vertical Beam Divergence","pageid":3006,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The angle of the light beam between points where the intensity has fallen to a fraction of the maximum intensity within the beam.\n</p><p>The vertical divergence is typically specified between the first points where the intensity falls to 50<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0bcef9c45bd8a48eda1b26eb0c61c869\">%</span> of the maximum.\n</p><p><br>\n</p>\n<figure class=\"mw-halign-none\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frame\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:VerticalBeamDivergencePlot.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/2/22/VerticalBeamDivergencePlot.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"576\" height=\"381\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a><figcaption>figure 1</figcaption></figure>\n<p><br>\nNote: In the past, lantern vertical divergence was defined as the angular separation of the upper and lower 10<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0bcef9c45bd8a48eda1b26eb0c61c869\">%</span> intensity points in the intensity profile Full Width Tenth Maximum (<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"2963f7c99b94df494783961a8e6aeb4e\">FWTM</span>).  More recently, lantern divergence has been defined by the Full Width Half Maximum (<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"d7d74f524f054fe5e0b1d048beb88165\">FWHM</span>) intensity, the angular separation of the upper and lower 50<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0bcef9c45bd8a48eda1b26eb0c61c869\">%</span> intensity points in the intensity profile.\n</p><p><br>\n</p><p><br>\nSource: ENG7, Guideline G1065\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Codes_on_Alerts_and_Indicators\" title=\"Codes on Alerts and Indicators\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0bcef9c45bd8a48eda1b26eb0c61c869\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>percent\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"2963f7c99b94df494783961a8e6aeb4e\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Full Width Tenth Maximum\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"d7d74f524f054fe5e0b1d048beb88165\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Full Width Half Maximum\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260616024114\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.039 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.057 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 58/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 733/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 398/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    9.821      1 Template:Languages\n100.00%    9.821      1 -total\n 68.25%    6.703      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:p